WEBVTT

00:02.380 --> 00:04.380
Kevin: My life was going
pretty terrible.

00:04.380 --> 00:06.710
I lost my job, had to move in
with my sister and my niece,

00:06.710 --> 00:08.710
and then things got weird.

00:08.710 --> 00:11.120
I wouldn't do that.

00:11.880 --> 00:13.790
Super weird.

00:13.790 --> 00:15.380
-Am I still asleep?
-No.

00:15.380 --> 00:18.330
Yvette: In every generation,
there are 36 righteous souls.

00:18.330 --> 00:20.330
You are the last
of the righteous.

00:20.330 --> 00:23.500
You are on a mission to bring
balance to the universe.

00:23.500 --> 00:24.500
Who are you talking to?

00:24.500 --> 00:26.120
She can't see me.

00:26.120 --> 00:30.500
She's done a pretty good job
convincing me she's real.

00:30.500 --> 00:33.620
And now I have to do something
I haven't had to do before --

00:33.620 --> 00:37.210
put others before myself,
help people.

00:37.210 --> 00:39.830
I am the last guy you'd
ever want to save the world,

00:39.830 --> 00:41.960
but I think
I can figure it out...

00:41.960 --> 00:43.460
probably.

00:46.500 --> 00:48.500
[ Rooster crows ]

00:48.500 --> 00:55.380
♪♪

00:55.380 --> 00:58.540
Okay. Have a good day.
I'll pick you up this afternoon.

00:58.540 --> 01:01.920
[ Phone chirps ]
Uh, I have drama, so I'll
just get a ride with Emma.

01:01.920 --> 01:03.290
Did you see my lunch?

01:03.290 --> 01:04.880
Nope.

01:04.880 --> 01:07.250
What is this?

01:07.250 --> 01:09.540
It's not a big deal,
okay, so --

01:09.540 --> 01:11.880
"Reese Cabrera has sent you
a friend request

01:11.880 --> 01:12.920
on the WePeeps network"?

01:12.920 --> 01:14.620
Oh, my God.

01:14.620 --> 01:15.790
Just don't!

01:15.790 --> 01:17.420
Reese. I am so touched.

01:17.420 --> 01:18.670
[ Scoffs ]
Never mind.

01:18.670 --> 01:20.170
No, this is huge
for me, really.

01:20.170 --> 01:21.420
For us, as a family.

01:21.420 --> 01:23.330
Forget it.
Hit "ignore."

01:23.330 --> 01:25.380
You know what, I'm not gonna hit
"accept" just yet

01:25.380 --> 01:27.250
because I want to savor
this notification.

01:27.250 --> 01:28.790
♪♪

01:28.790 --> 01:30.960
Okay, I'm accepting.
I just hit "accept."

01:30.960 --> 01:32.580
[ Phone chimes ]
Oh! We're friends!

01:32.580 --> 01:33.880
You and me!

01:33.880 --> 01:35.920
That girl there
just friended me.

01:35.920 --> 01:38.750
I get you all the way

01:38.750 --> 01:40.580
In my home

01:40.580 --> 01:42.620
It ain't open

01:42.620 --> 01:45.040
It's a short way

01:45.040 --> 01:47.210
My home

01:47.210 --> 01:48.880
Wide open

01:48.880 --> 01:51.880
I get you all the way

01:51.880 --> 01:53.880
My home

01:53.880 --> 01:55.790
It ain't open

01:55.790 --> 01:58.330
It's a short way

01:58.330 --> 02:00.250
I just feel like
there's a bunch of things

02:00.250 --> 02:01.460
we haven't talked about.

02:01.460 --> 02:02.790
Such as?

02:02.790 --> 02:05.460
I mean, everything.

02:05.460 --> 02:07.250
What does God look like?

02:07.250 --> 02:10.080
What happens when you die?
Aliens.

02:12.330 --> 02:13.710
Wait, are there aliens?

02:13.710 --> 02:15.580
Your face looks like
there might be aliens.

02:15.580 --> 02:18.580
Are you done?
'Cause you need to get to work.

02:18.580 --> 02:21.750
You know, find someone
the universe wants to help.

02:21.750 --> 02:25.210
Wow, somebody put on
their cranky pants today.

02:27.460 --> 02:29.460
Okay, I'll go.

02:29.460 --> 02:32.710
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:32.710 --> 02:34.420
So, are we talking,
like, ET or Predator?

02:34.420 --> 02:36.290
Go.

02:36.290 --> 02:37.540
Go!

02:37.540 --> 02:41.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:41.920 --> 02:44.000
[ Bells jingle ]

02:48.170 --> 02:49.620
[ Door creaks ]

02:49.620 --> 02:51.420
[ Grunts ]

02:53.790 --> 02:55.620
What the hell
are you doing in here?

02:55.620 --> 02:58.210
Oh, uh, sorry.
I got turned around.

02:58.210 --> 02:59.960
[ Mocking ] "Oh, sorry.
I'm an idiot."

02:59.960 --> 03:01.250
Get out of here!

03:01.250 --> 03:03.670
Is there another exit
I could use?

03:03.670 --> 03:05.920
-Would you like a map?
-Uh --

03:05.920 --> 03:08.080
Get out of my kitchen
or I'm calling the cops!

03:08.080 --> 03:10.670
Okay!

03:10.670 --> 03:11.710
Is there a problem?

03:11.710 --> 03:14.330
Um, maybe. Could be.
I don't know.

03:14.330 --> 03:16.120
Hi. I'll be...

03:16.120 --> 03:20.290
♪♪

03:20.290 --> 03:21.960
Woman: Hey, buddy!
This is the ladies' room!

03:21.960 --> 03:23.460
Kevin:
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

03:23.460 --> 03:25.880
That...was a total accident.
-Get out of here, you creep!

03:25.880 --> 03:26.960
[ Door closes ]

03:29.250 --> 03:30.710
[ Clears throat ]

03:32.500 --> 03:35.540
You know what, I think the
universe wants me to stay here.

03:40.620 --> 03:43.670
[ Clears throat ]
Okay, so my job is here.

03:43.670 --> 03:46.750
Wonder who it is.

03:46.750 --> 03:48.830
Tyler:
Hey, Lucille, check it out.

03:48.830 --> 03:51.040
Someone didn't clean up
after their dog.

03:51.040 --> 03:52.620
You know what that means?

03:52.620 --> 03:54.670
That you should have left
your shoe outside.

03:54.670 --> 03:57.460
It means today
is my lucky day!

03:57.460 --> 03:59.460
Hey, Kev!
-Hey!

04:02.120 --> 04:04.620
[ Gasps ]
Of course!

04:05.880 --> 04:08.080
Tyler.

04:08.080 --> 04:10.790
Got to help Tyler.

04:10.790 --> 04:13.580
[ Sighs ]

04:13.580 --> 04:15.380
This is cool.

04:19.420 --> 04:22.420
Man, It's so awesome
that you're thinking of me,

04:22.420 --> 04:24.120
but I couldn't be
any happier.

04:24.120 --> 04:25.920
Seriously.

04:25.920 --> 04:29.080
It's just that a lot of bad
things tend to happen to you.

04:29.080 --> 04:30.500
Like what?

04:30.500 --> 04:32.500
Your divorce.
You're living with your mom.

04:32.500 --> 04:33.790
This place.

04:33.790 --> 04:36.620
Uh, meant to be,
living with my best friend,

04:36.620 --> 04:38.420
doing what
I'm meant to do.

04:38.420 --> 04:40.920
Didn't realize I was
operating a soup kitchen

04:40.920 --> 04:42.380
for online predators.

04:42.380 --> 04:43.540
Are you?

04:43.540 --> 04:45.460
Well, I have a sack
of wet socks

04:45.460 --> 04:47.710
serving unlimited refills
to a creep.

04:47.710 --> 04:51.120
[ Laughs ] You're too funny.
Am I the sock sack?

04:51.120 --> 04:53.330
Listen, if perv stache here
doesn't order

04:53.330 --> 04:55.500
something expensive or get out,
you're fired.

04:55.500 --> 04:57.330
[ Chuckles ]

04:57.330 --> 04:58.880
Perv stache?

04:58.880 --> 05:00.250
Classic Lucille.

05:00.250 --> 05:02.420
Does she always
treat you like that?

05:02.420 --> 05:04.830
Oh, no, that's our thing.
We bust on each other.

05:04.830 --> 05:05.960
It's banter.

05:05.960 --> 05:07.210
Do you bust on her?

05:07.210 --> 05:08.500
Oh, no,
she'd take my head off.

05:08.500 --> 05:09.880
[ Scoffs ]

05:09.880 --> 05:11.880
Tyler, you're a nice guy.

05:11.880 --> 05:13.420
Thanks, man.

05:13.420 --> 05:14.920
No, no, no, no.
That is not good.

05:14.920 --> 05:16.620
This world is not meant
for nice guys.

05:16.620 --> 05:18.380
This world
eats up nice guys.

05:18.380 --> 05:21.040
I can only be me, Kev.

05:21.040 --> 05:24.210
Yeah, I know.
I can't help you there.

05:24.210 --> 05:27.080
But I can help you
do one thing.

05:27.080 --> 05:28.750
You have to get a new job.

05:28.750 --> 05:31.580
Oh, no way, man.
I love this job!

05:31.580 --> 05:33.500
-[ Sighs ]
-I meet interesting customers.

05:33.500 --> 05:36.330
I get a discount on food
that's only slightly expired.

05:36.330 --> 05:39.250
And it's super-close to my
house, so I don't need a car.

05:39.250 --> 05:42.710
But if you had a car, then you
could work any place, hmm?

05:42.710 --> 05:44.420
I guess.

05:44.420 --> 05:46.000
But why would I?

05:46.000 --> 05:48.170
How much money
do you have?

05:48.170 --> 05:52.330
♪♪

05:52.330 --> 05:55.460
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:55.460 --> 06:01.960
♪♪

06:01.960 --> 06:03.210
Hey, Reese.

06:03.210 --> 06:05.460
See you at drama in a few?

06:05.460 --> 06:09.580
I actually have to go home.
My mom needs help with stuff.

06:09.580 --> 06:11.040
Is everything okay?

06:11.040 --> 06:12.420
It's fine.
Everything's fine.

06:12.420 --> 06:14.250
All right.
But we'll miss you.

06:14.250 --> 06:15.670
See you tomorrow, okay?

06:15.670 --> 06:20.620
♪♪

06:20.620 --> 06:22.540
♪ Play it again ♪

06:22.540 --> 06:25.670
♪♪

06:25.670 --> 06:27.710
♪ P-P-Play it again ♪

06:27.710 --> 06:30.710
It's a Chevy, low mileage.
The guy is asking $2,000.

06:30.710 --> 06:32.250
Sounds great.

06:32.250 --> 06:33.960
Yeah, but you're not
paying $2,000.

06:33.960 --> 06:36.500
No more than $1,500.

06:36.500 --> 06:38.580
Oh, man, I don't
really like to bargain.

06:38.580 --> 06:40.580
I'll just pay the deuce,
call it a day.

06:40.580 --> 06:42.710
See, this is what
I'm talking about.

06:42.710 --> 06:45.080
You let everybody take
advantage of you.

06:45.080 --> 06:47.210
I want you to stand up
for yourself.

06:47.210 --> 06:49.670
I'll help you get this car,
and then you can quit.

06:49.670 --> 06:54.710
♪♪

06:54.710 --> 07:00.670
♪♪

07:00.670 --> 07:03.290
Okay, I'll negotiate.

07:03.290 --> 07:06.250
Start low, hear his counter,
find the middle ground.

07:06.250 --> 07:07.830
$1,500, guaranteed.

07:07.830 --> 07:09.670
Let's do it now.

07:09.670 --> 07:11.330
-Hey.
-Hey. You Zack?

07:11.330 --> 07:12.830
-Yeah.
-I'm here about the car.

07:12.830 --> 07:14.290
-How's it going?
-Hey, man.

07:14.290 --> 07:16.460
[ Clears throat ]
So, I was comparing prices

07:16.460 --> 07:18.540
to other similar models,
and I --

07:18.540 --> 07:21.330
Yeah, so, if you want it,
I'll give it to you for $900.

07:21.330 --> 07:23.080
[ Whispering ]
Oh, my God, you're good.

07:23.080 --> 07:24.790
I'm sorry.
How much now?

07:24.790 --> 07:26.670
$900.
What can I say?

07:26.670 --> 07:28.580
I need the cash.
We got a deal?

07:28.580 --> 07:31.960
Uh, yeah. Yeah.

07:31.960 --> 07:34.170
I mean, we'll have to
drive it first.

07:34.170 --> 07:36.080
Yeah, sure. Come on.
I'll get you the keys.

07:38.540 --> 07:39.750
Ohh!

07:39.750 --> 07:44.210
♪♪

07:44.210 --> 07:48.670
♪♪

07:48.670 --> 07:53.120
♪♪

07:53.120 --> 07:56.250
Hmm, that was some mean
negotiating, Kevin.

07:56.250 --> 07:59.000
Maybe we should send you
to the Middle East.

07:59.000 --> 08:03.120
Okay, will you please tell me
what is going on with you?

08:04.750 --> 08:08.170
I slept for five minutes
last night.

08:08.170 --> 08:10.250
Ah. Insomnia.

08:10.250 --> 08:11.790
No wonder you're crabby.

08:11.790 --> 08:13.170
Mnh-mnh.
You don't understand.

08:13.170 --> 08:14.460
I don't sleep.

08:14.460 --> 08:15.460
Never?

08:15.460 --> 08:16.420
Ever.

08:16.420 --> 08:17.710
Well, have you ever spent

08:17.710 --> 08:19.420
this much time
here on Earth?

08:19.420 --> 08:21.670
No, and I-I think
that's the problem.

08:21.670 --> 08:23.670
Too much time with...
people.

08:23.670 --> 08:25.120
You're rubbing off on me.

08:25.120 --> 08:28.250
I think sleep is awesome.

08:28.250 --> 08:29.790
It's one
of my favorite things.

08:29.790 --> 08:31.170
[ Sighs ]

08:31.170 --> 08:33.080
Probably top three.
Maybe number one.

08:33.080 --> 08:36.120
It's a waste of time,
and it'll be the last time.

08:38.460 --> 08:41.040
[ Sighs ]
You're missing out.

08:41.040 --> 08:44.540
I could name 100 things
about sleep that I love.

08:44.540 --> 08:46.420
It is literally the best.

08:46.420 --> 08:49.210
Uh, because of dreams,
obviously.

08:49.210 --> 08:51.420
You can do whatever
you want.

08:51.420 --> 08:53.080
Dude, I got the keys!

08:55.330 --> 08:57.620
-[ Chuckles ]
-[ Chuckles ]

08:57.620 --> 08:59.250
[ Engine starts ]

08:59.250 --> 09:01.790
Aw! Listen to her purr!

09:01.790 --> 09:04.500
Oh, there's a CD player!
Sweet!

09:04.500 --> 09:05.790
Yeah. It's not bad.

09:05.790 --> 09:07.250
And Zack is so nice.

09:07.250 --> 09:08.920
We're gonna go grab coffee
later.

09:08.920 --> 09:10.040
New friend!

09:10.040 --> 09:12.120
[ Chuckles ]
It's cool.

09:12.120 --> 09:15.290
Kevin, I want to thank you
for looking out for me.

09:15.290 --> 09:18.290
I didn't even know I needed
this, but I did.

09:18.290 --> 09:20.250
You're awesome, man.

09:20.250 --> 09:22.210
You're awesome, man.
[ Chuckles ]

09:25.210 --> 09:26.420
[ Tires screech ]

09:26.420 --> 09:28.790
[ Grunts ]

09:28.790 --> 09:32.330
[ High-pitched ringing ]

09:32.330 --> 09:34.000
[ Breathing heavily ]

09:35.330 --> 09:36.670
Are you...?

09:39.330 --> 09:42.420
You don't make
protecting you easy.

09:42.420 --> 09:44.250
Tyler!

09:46.710 --> 09:50.250
♪♪

09:50.250 --> 09:54.460
♪♪

09:54.460 --> 09:59.040
Wow!
This car -- so safe!

09:59.040 --> 10:01.750
[ Both breathing heavily ]

10:01.750 --> 10:04.040
[ Metal clanks ]

10:09.120 --> 10:11.460
[ Chuckles ]
It's not a problem, Kevin.

10:11.460 --> 10:13.540
Zack's insurance
is paying more for the car

10:13.540 --> 10:14.790
than he'd ever get
selling it.

10:14.790 --> 10:16.040
Everybody wins!

10:16.040 --> 10:17.960
You don't.
You don't have a car,

10:17.960 --> 10:20.080
and now you're still stuck
working here.

10:20.080 --> 10:21.380
You have to quit.

10:21.380 --> 10:22.580
I can't quit.

10:22.580 --> 10:24.250
People count on me.

10:24.250 --> 10:26.210
Okay, I-I-I got it.
I got it.

10:26.210 --> 10:28.620
I-I have no doubt
that you are indispensable,

10:28.620 --> 10:29.880
but you can do better.

10:29.880 --> 10:32.620
I don't want to.

10:32.620 --> 10:34.420
Plus, Lucille.

10:34.420 --> 10:36.170
She'd be crushed.

10:36.170 --> 10:37.960
Would she?
Let's ask her.

10:37.960 --> 10:39.540
Lucille!
Hey, Kevin.

10:39.540 --> 10:42.420
Hey. Stop being a good guy
and stand up for yourself.

10:42.420 --> 10:44.380
What have I said
about calling for me?

10:44.380 --> 10:47.170
You walk to me.
I don't walk to you.

10:47.170 --> 10:49.210
Tyler, do you have something
to say to Lucille?

10:52.080 --> 10:55.750
Kevin, I'm gonna take your
advice and stand up for myself.

10:55.750 --> 10:59.710
You're awesome,
but I don't need your help.

10:59.710 --> 11:01.330
Excuse me?

11:01.330 --> 11:02.790
I need help.

11:02.790 --> 11:04.330
What did you say?

11:04.330 --> 11:05.380
What, are you deaf?

11:05.380 --> 11:07.080
I said I need help!
[ Slams counter ]

11:08.880 --> 11:11.460
Someone needs to help me!

11:11.460 --> 11:12.790
Are you gonna help me?

11:12.790 --> 11:13.880
[ Electricity humming ]

11:13.880 --> 11:15.500
Oh, no. It's you.

11:20.500 --> 11:21.670
This is wrong.

11:21.670 --> 11:23.790
Tyler's the one
who needs an overhaul.

11:23.790 --> 11:25.710
Tyler is fine
as far as I can tell.

11:25.710 --> 11:27.960
Why does the universe want me
to help someone like Lucille?

11:27.960 --> 11:30.500
You don't know what's
going on in her life.

11:30.500 --> 11:32.750
A kind gesture could
change her entire outlook.

11:32.750 --> 11:34.540
But she's awful.

11:34.540 --> 11:37.000
Oh, I don't know.

11:37.000 --> 11:39.830
She's kind of fun.

11:39.830 --> 11:42.000
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:45.880 --> 11:47.710
[ Clears throat ]

11:47.710 --> 11:49.460
Hi, uh, well,
let's get this part

11:49.460 --> 11:51.250
out of the way up front --
I am an idiot

11:51.250 --> 11:54.620
and a waste of space
and an ass boil.

11:54.620 --> 11:57.380
I'm listening.

11:57.380 --> 11:59.380
Uh, well, you said
you needed help.

11:59.380 --> 12:03.120
And I am here to help you
with whatever you need.

12:03.120 --> 12:04.500
Is this a con job?

12:04.500 --> 12:05.960
Nope.

12:05.960 --> 12:09.210
Have a seat.

12:09.210 --> 12:11.830
[ Clears throat ]

12:11.830 --> 12:13.540
So, what is it
you need done?

12:13.540 --> 12:15.540
Maybe something that's
been weighing on you,

12:15.540 --> 12:17.960
something that might
change your whole outlook.

12:17.960 --> 12:19.920
There is one thing.

12:19.920 --> 12:21.380
Oh, great. Name it.

12:21.380 --> 12:22.580
I have an antique clock
in storage.

12:22.580 --> 12:23.620
Get it.

12:23.620 --> 12:25.920
That's it?
Just move a clock?

12:25.920 --> 12:27.170
It's a family heirloom,

12:27.170 --> 12:28.880
and it's worth more
than your pathetic life.

12:33.830 --> 12:36.080
I've had to move it
the last couple of years

12:36.080 --> 12:38.000
because of certain unsavory
family members

12:38.000 --> 12:39.420
who keep trying to steal it.

12:39.420 --> 12:42.000
Hmm.
I'd feel better
if it's in my house.

12:42.000 --> 12:43.670
Mm.

12:43.670 --> 12:46.710
I'm trusting you with something
that's very important to me.

12:46.710 --> 12:48.880
Can I feel confident that
you're not gonna screw it up?

12:48.880 --> 12:52.040
Yeah.

12:52.040 --> 12:55.830
♪♪

12:55.830 --> 12:58.670
[ Door creaks, closes ]

12:58.670 --> 13:00.670
♪♪

13:00.670 --> 13:02.500
Hey.

13:02.500 --> 13:03.790
Hey.

13:03.790 --> 13:05.330
Uh, is Tyler okay?

13:05.330 --> 13:09.460
He's a little shaken up,
but he's -- he's fine.

13:09.460 --> 13:10.670
You're not hurt.

13:10.670 --> 13:13.210
Like, at all.

13:13.210 --> 13:15.170
Lucky.

13:15.170 --> 13:17.120
Your seat just
came out of the car.

13:17.120 --> 13:18.790
How did that happen?

13:20.580 --> 13:21.960
Physics.

13:24.290 --> 13:27.380
It was probably,
um, physics.

13:28.670 --> 13:31.670
What were you doing
in that neighborhood?

13:35.210 --> 13:37.620
My friend lives there.

13:37.620 --> 13:39.790
Hey.

13:39.790 --> 13:41.790
So I was thinking
lasagna for dinner.

13:41.790 --> 13:43.460
Sound good?

13:43.460 --> 13:46.380
Uh, I got to get going, but I'll
just grab something later.

13:46.380 --> 13:48.580
Hey, Reese, I ran into Emma's
mom at the supermarket.

13:48.580 --> 13:49.920
She said you weren't
in drama.

13:52.380 --> 13:55.580
I wasn't feeling well,
so I just came home.

13:55.580 --> 13:56.670
Hmm.

13:56.670 --> 13:58.580
Yeah, I heard something's
going around.

13:58.580 --> 14:00.620
Oh.

14:00.620 --> 14:03.210
Well, maybe just some broth
and toast for you.

14:03.210 --> 14:07.750
Mmm! Delicious.

14:07.750 --> 14:09.750
I hope you get better.

14:09.750 --> 14:11.620
[ Coughs ]

14:11.620 --> 14:12.790
Uh-oh.

14:12.790 --> 14:13.960
[ Coughs ]

14:15.540 --> 14:20.000
♪♪

14:20.000 --> 14:24.750
♪♪

14:24.750 --> 14:27.330
What are the odds Lucille
ditched a body in here?

14:27.330 --> 14:29.750
Stop complaining
and get to work.

14:29.750 --> 14:32.120
I know that you
don't like sleep,

14:32.120 --> 14:34.920
but I think you should
give it another chance.

14:34.920 --> 14:36.500
At least a little nap.

14:36.500 --> 14:38.620
[ Sighs ]
I had a dream.

14:38.620 --> 14:40.750
Last night,
when I fell asleep.

14:40.750 --> 14:44.380
Like, involving you and your
cousin in a weird way?

14:46.000 --> 14:48.210
No? Okay.

14:48.210 --> 14:50.380
[ Sighs ]
I dreamt of home.

14:50.380 --> 14:52.170
What's it like there?

14:52.170 --> 14:54.620
I couldn't begin to explain.

14:56.250 --> 14:58.540
You're homesick.

14:58.540 --> 15:02.290
I-I was really homesick when
I first moved to New York.

15:02.290 --> 15:06.380
Um, but I could
visit any time.

15:06.380 --> 15:08.290
You don't really
have that option.

15:08.290 --> 15:10.040
Thank you for spelling
it out for me.

15:12.000 --> 15:17.080
You know what, I found
a honkytonk bar in Brooklyn.

15:17.080 --> 15:19.880
It was terrible music,
so-so barbecue,

15:19.880 --> 15:21.710
but it reminded me of home.

15:21.710 --> 15:24.580
Is there anything here
that reminds you of home?

15:24.580 --> 15:26.250
Nothing.

15:26.250 --> 15:27.830
Clouds?

15:27.830 --> 15:31.580
Newborn baby?

15:31.580 --> 15:33.120
Music?

15:33.120 --> 15:34.290
Nothing.

15:34.290 --> 15:35.670
Well, maybe you should,
uh --

15:35.670 --> 15:37.670
Maybe you should meet up
with your colleagues again.

15:37.670 --> 15:39.290
I bet they all feel
the same way.

15:39.290 --> 15:41.380
Look, it's not necessary.
I just need to stay awake.

15:41.380 --> 15:43.080
Okay.

15:45.750 --> 15:48.500
[ Clattering ]

15:48.500 --> 15:50.170
There's a dead rat.

15:50.170 --> 15:51.290
There's a dead rat
right in there.

15:52.710 --> 15:53.540
I touched it.

15:55.170 --> 15:57.000
[ Retches ]

15:58.620 --> 16:00.670
[ Sighs ]

16:00.670 --> 16:02.750
Here it is.

16:04.580 --> 16:06.080
Thank you.

16:06.080 --> 16:07.210
Mm-hmm.

16:08.750 --> 16:12.290
Daddy was in the service.
He brought it over from Germany.

16:12.290 --> 16:15.170
Every day he'd wind it
and tell me and my sister

16:15.170 --> 16:17.040
stories about
all his adventures.

16:17.040 --> 16:18.670
♪♪

16:18.670 --> 16:22.500
When he died,
my sister took everything.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.790
♪♪

16:24.790 --> 16:26.960
[ Voice breaking ] This is
all I have left of him.

16:28.420 --> 16:31.210
Well, I'm -- I'm glad
I was able to help.

16:31.210 --> 16:34.670
[ Sniffs ]
Where are you gonna put it?

16:34.670 --> 16:36.960
[ Clears throat ]

16:36.960 --> 16:39.460
Somewhere between "It's none
of your freaking business"

16:39.460 --> 16:41.210
and "Stop asking me
so many questions."

16:41.210 --> 16:43.580
Okay. I bet it'll look
really good there.

16:48.710 --> 16:50.080
[ Engine starts ]

16:50.080 --> 16:52.040
You got Lucille's clock.

16:52.040 --> 16:54.290
I did.

16:54.290 --> 16:56.710
Maybe she'll be a little nicer
from now on.

16:56.710 --> 16:58.420
I mean, probably not.
But...

16:58.420 --> 17:01.380
You made Lucille
really happy.

17:01.380 --> 17:03.750
Looks like you're a nice guy,
too, Mr. Finn.

17:03.750 --> 17:05.620
[ Both chuckle ]

17:05.620 --> 17:08.380
Still can't believe you stole
that clock, though.

17:08.380 --> 17:10.670
[ Chuckles ]

17:10.670 --> 17:12.620
I'm sorry. Stole it?

17:12.620 --> 17:15.040
Oh, yeah, she's been trying
to get me to steal that

17:15.040 --> 17:16.620
from her sister
for years.

17:16.620 --> 17:19.210
I always draw the line
at criminal activity,

17:19.210 --> 17:20.920
but you don't have a problem
with that.

17:20.920 --> 17:22.210
That was so cool.

17:22.210 --> 17:24.170
That was her sister's
storage unit?

17:24.170 --> 17:27.040
Yeah.
It's worth like 20 grand.

17:27.040 --> 17:29.000
Which means
I just committed a felony.

17:30.210 --> 17:33.080
Hey.
Go big or go home, right?

17:38.790 --> 17:41.120
What are you doing?

17:41.120 --> 17:43.120
Watching
"Kitten Fail" videos.

17:44.500 --> 17:46.620
It's cute, right?

17:46.620 --> 17:49.250
What about Lucille?

17:49.250 --> 17:52.330
Do you have the term
"dead to me" where you're from?

17:52.330 --> 17:53.750
Because she is that.

17:53.750 --> 17:56.120
I am done with Lucille.

17:56.120 --> 17:57.750
Have you gotten
your vision yet?

17:57.750 --> 18:00.830
Oh, my God.

18:00.830 --> 18:04.710
I've just been transported
somewhere --

18:04.710 --> 18:06.380
somewhere exotic.

18:06.380 --> 18:08.960
There -- Oh, wow!

18:08.960 --> 18:11.790
Look at all these...
people

18:11.790 --> 18:13.920
who are indigenous
to this region.

18:13.920 --> 18:18.380
Kevin...I'm tired, and I do not
have time for this.

18:18.380 --> 18:21.170
You need to finish the job.

18:21.170 --> 18:23.000
I'm gonna take
a hard pass on that.

18:23.000 --> 18:24.040
[ Clears throat ]

18:24.040 --> 18:25.670
She needs you.

18:25.670 --> 18:27.500
She needs a jail cell.

18:27.500 --> 18:29.620
She had me steal for her.

18:29.620 --> 18:31.880
Lucille's a criminal
and now I'm one, too,

18:31.880 --> 18:34.000
and I'm not going to jail
over a clock.

18:34.000 --> 18:35.960
I don't think
this is about a clock.

18:35.960 --> 18:38.330
Maybe it's about repairing
Lucille's relationship

18:38.330 --> 18:39.710
with her sister.

18:39.710 --> 18:42.750
Well, that relationship
should never be repaired.

18:42.750 --> 18:45.750
Her sister should join witness
protection and disappear.

18:45.750 --> 18:47.290
You're very judgmental.

18:47.290 --> 18:49.670
I don't think I realized this
about you.

18:49.670 --> 18:52.080
Look, why don't we just
wait this one out,

18:52.080 --> 18:54.170
and eventually the universe
will send

18:54.170 --> 18:56.460
a needy but less terrible
person my way.

18:56.460 --> 18:59.170
So you only help people
who deserve it.

18:59.170 --> 19:01.080
Yeah.

19:01.080 --> 19:04.210
And you get to judge
who's most deserving.

19:04.210 --> 19:05.920
Fine with that.

19:05.920 --> 19:08.460
Because you've been
such a good person.

19:08.460 --> 19:11.710
Whatever I've done,
I was never that bad.

19:11.710 --> 19:13.120
Kevin Finn!

19:13.120 --> 19:16.790
Kevin, Amy, which one
of you did this?

19:16.790 --> 19:19.120
Amy, you come with me.

19:19.120 --> 19:20.750
Big time out.

19:20.750 --> 19:22.620
But I don't even
know that word.

19:22.620 --> 19:28.500
♪♪

19:28.500 --> 19:30.920
I was 8.

19:30.920 --> 19:33.000
Give me a break.

19:33.000 --> 19:35.830
♪♪

19:35.830 --> 19:38.920
Now, Mrs. Thompkins,
no investment is risk-free,

19:38.920 --> 19:42.420
but there's a huge upside
to the sub-prime markets.

19:42.420 --> 19:44.710
Well, I think that is
a great choice,

19:44.710 --> 19:46.880
and I will put it through
tonight.

19:46.880 --> 19:49.540
Congratulations!
Okay.

19:49.540 --> 19:52.380
[ Sighs ]

19:52.380 --> 19:54.380
Guess who just squeezed
$50,000

19:54.380 --> 19:55.920
out of a 76-year-old
grandmother.

19:55.920 --> 19:57.170
[ Grunts ]

19:57.170 --> 20:00.000
$50,000!

20:00.000 --> 20:01.580
-Yeah!
-That's how you do it!

20:01.580 --> 20:03.420
That's how
you get it done!

20:03.420 --> 20:05.960
[ Laughter ]
$50,000.

20:08.750 --> 20:10.580
That was my old life.

20:10.580 --> 20:12.420
I'm not anything like
that guy anymore.

20:12.420 --> 20:14.250
$50,000!
Sure about that?

20:14.250 --> 20:17.000
Go!
[ Laughs ]

20:17.000 --> 20:21.250
♪♪

20:21.250 --> 20:23.330
Welcome
to this morning.

20:23.330 --> 20:26.170
♪♪

20:26.170 --> 20:29.330
Amy: Reese!
Don't forget your lunch!

20:29.330 --> 20:32.920
♪♪

20:32.920 --> 20:37.330
♪♪

20:37.330 --> 20:39.210
You've made
some excellent points.

20:40.620 --> 20:42.710
Still think Lucille's
beneath you?

20:42.710 --> 20:45.500
She is so mean.

20:45.500 --> 20:47.710
That's just the pain
she's covering.

20:47.710 --> 20:49.880
Underneath is someone
looking for help.

20:49.880 --> 20:52.880
Or more meanness.

20:52.880 --> 20:54.290
The worst people sometimes

20:54.290 --> 20:56.460
are the ones who need
the most kindness.

20:56.460 --> 20:58.540
Everyone deserves a chance
to be better, Kevin.

20:58.540 --> 21:00.120
You got one.

21:00.120 --> 21:02.290
Fine, but I don't even know
where to start.

21:02.290 --> 21:05.120
Sure you do.

21:05.120 --> 21:07.420
You lied to me,
Lucille.

21:07.420 --> 21:10.460
I did not lie.
This clock belongs to me.

21:10.460 --> 21:13.000
Daddy said it was mine,
and Ann took it.

21:13.000 --> 21:14.670
Well, then, talk to her.

21:14.670 --> 21:17.210
I haven't spoken to her
in 20 years.

21:17.210 --> 21:18.880
Well, what if
I talked to her?

21:18.880 --> 21:22.120
Fine. Be my guest.
Y-You think I'm a hard-ass?

21:22.120 --> 21:23.670
She's a monster.

21:23.670 --> 21:25.330
[ Knock on door ]

21:25.330 --> 21:29.750
Hi, my name is Kevin Finn.
Are you Ann?

21:29.750 --> 21:31.120
Yes. Can I help you?

21:31.120 --> 21:33.380
Uh, well, I'm here
about your sister.

21:33.380 --> 21:36.170
Oh, no.
Is Lucille okay?

21:36.170 --> 21:41.290
Oh. Yeah. Yeah. Yeah, yep.
She's healthy as a...snake.

21:41.290 --> 21:43.500
Do you mind if I talk
to you for a minute?

21:43.500 --> 21:45.330
We were best friends.

21:45.330 --> 21:48.080
I don't even remember
what drove us apart.

21:48.080 --> 21:49.620
But she's made it
crystal clear

21:49.620 --> 21:51.710
she doesn't want to have
anything to do with me.

21:51.710 --> 21:54.830
Well, people can change.
Sometimes.

21:54.830 --> 21:56.880
And Lucille's changed?

21:56.880 --> 22:00.380
Well, I said "can" --
can change.

22:00.380 --> 22:01.830
The things she's said
to me.

22:01.830 --> 22:03.380
You wouldn't believe.

22:03.380 --> 22:04.790
I'm sure
I can believe a little.

22:04.790 --> 22:07.500
She's selfish.
She's a liar.

22:07.500 --> 22:10.460
And because of her, I never got
to see my father before he died.

22:10.460 --> 22:12.250
Why not?

22:12.250 --> 22:14.540
He got sick,
and Ann took over.

22:14.540 --> 22:16.750
She wouldn't even let me
come visit him.

22:16.750 --> 22:19.420
I didn't even know he died
until a day later.

22:19.420 --> 22:21.830
I begged her to come home
when Daddy was sick,

22:21.830 --> 22:24.330
but she didn't want to believe
that he was gonna die.

22:24.330 --> 22:28.420
And then...
it was too late.

22:28.420 --> 22:31.330
By that time, she'd just
cleared out his entire house.

22:31.330 --> 22:34.000
I had nothing
to remember him by.

22:34.000 --> 22:37.380
All I wanted was that clock,
and she knew it.

22:37.380 --> 22:39.290
Do you really want to
go through your whole life

22:39.290 --> 22:40.750
without speaking
to your sister?

22:42.330 --> 22:43.670
I know I wouldn't.

22:43.670 --> 22:45.330
It's up to her.

22:45.330 --> 22:49.620
If she says yes...
then maybe.

22:49.620 --> 22:52.420
I think
Lucille is in pain,

22:52.420 --> 22:56.790
and I think the only thing
that will help

22:56.790 --> 23:00.420
is reconnecting
with her sister.

23:00.420 --> 23:02.420
Hmm.

23:02.420 --> 23:06.620
If she agreed to sit down
with you, would you do it?

23:06.620 --> 23:09.580
Yes. I would.

23:09.580 --> 23:10.620
Great.

23:10.620 --> 23:13.290
That is -- That's --
That's great.

23:13.290 --> 23:15.380
I will make it happen.

23:15.380 --> 23:17.920
'Cause an old clock
with a broken minute hand

23:17.920 --> 23:19.790
isn't worth
giving up your family.

23:19.790 --> 23:22.080
How do you know
about the clock?

23:22.080 --> 23:24.210
[ Clears throat ]

23:24.210 --> 23:27.250
[ Chuckles ] That's kind of
a funny story, actually.

23:27.250 --> 23:29.750
Um, I accidentally
stole it for Lucille.

23:29.750 --> 23:31.330
You stole my clock.

23:31.330 --> 23:32.920
Accidentally.
But the important thing

23:32.920 --> 23:35.290
is making up with your sister
and building that bond again.

23:35.290 --> 23:37.460
I knew it!
What kind of scam

23:37.460 --> 23:40.330
are you and that twisted
goblin whore running?!

23:40.330 --> 23:42.580
Nothing! No scam!
I was -- I was trying to help!

23:42.580 --> 23:44.790
Lucille has been ruining my life
since we were kids.

23:44.790 --> 23:47.670
Mm-hmm.
And now she's hired this
low-rent gigolo to rip me off!

23:47.670 --> 23:48.750
Low-rent?

23:48.750 --> 23:51.000
That clock is mine.

23:51.000 --> 23:52.330
Well, I really think
if you just sat down

23:52.330 --> 23:54.170
and talked about it
for a little bit, then --

23:54.170 --> 23:55.540
I really think,
you dopey-eyed Chihuahua,

23:55.540 --> 23:58.750
you better get
my clock back tonight!

23:58.750 --> 24:01.710
And if you don't, I am calling
the cops on both of you.

24:01.710 --> 24:02.920
-Wow.
-Get me?

24:02.920 --> 24:04.710
-Mm-hmm.
-Yeah, I think that maybe

24:04.710 --> 24:06.000
Lucille can hack it,

24:06.000 --> 24:08.540
but you don't look like
you're built for prison!

24:08.540 --> 24:10.250
Mnh-mnh.

24:10.250 --> 24:11.580
Go!

24:11.580 --> 24:12.500
Okay!

24:15.620 --> 24:16.830
[ Phone pings ]

24:16.830 --> 24:20.920
All right, Kevin,
where are we going tonight?

24:20.920 --> 24:22.920
-Amy: Hey, honey.
-Hi.

24:22.920 --> 24:25.210
-All right.
-What's that for?

24:25.210 --> 24:27.040
You said you
weren't feeling well.

24:27.040 --> 24:29.580
I'm not. I...

24:29.580 --> 24:31.580
It comes and goes.

24:31.580 --> 24:33.250
Right now
it's mostly in my throat.

24:33.250 --> 24:35.880
Should we get you checked out?
You think it might be strep?

24:35.880 --> 24:37.960
No, it's just scratchy.

24:37.960 --> 24:39.880
Let me see.
Come on. Open up.

24:39.880 --> 24:41.460
Ahh.

24:41.460 --> 24:43.210
Huh. Oh, yeah.

24:43.210 --> 24:45.750
You know what, I see a little
something back there.

24:45.750 --> 24:48.920
You know what, Reese, I'm gonna
cancel my 7:00 p.m. class,

24:48.920 --> 24:50.540
and I'm taking you
to urgent care.

24:50.540 --> 24:52.830
What?!
No, I just need to go to bed.

24:52.830 --> 24:54.380
Go to your class.

24:54.380 --> 24:56.620
[ Sighs ] I don't like leaving
you like this.

24:56.620 --> 25:00.040
It's fine.
I just need some sleep.

25:00.040 --> 25:01.580
I'll be better in the morning.

25:01.580 --> 25:03.750
All right.

25:03.750 --> 25:05.210
I will have
my phone on me.

25:05.210 --> 25:07.040
If you need anything,
call me, okay, or Kevin.

25:07.040 --> 25:08.670
No, don't call Kevin.

25:08.670 --> 25:10.500
If you need anything
and you can't get ahold of me,

25:10.500 --> 25:11.880
just keep calling and calling
and calling.

25:11.880 --> 25:13.830
-Go.
-Okay, okay, okay.

25:13.830 --> 25:16.000
I'll be asleep
a minute after you leave.

25:22.250 --> 25:24.500
[ Engine stops ]

25:29.250 --> 25:31.170
What's this outfit
supposed to be?

25:31.170 --> 25:32.620
You know what, I'm sorry
if you don't like

25:32.620 --> 25:33.960
my breaking-and-entering
clothes,

25:33.960 --> 25:35.120
but it's what I
could get together

25:35.120 --> 25:36.210
in a short amount
of time.

25:36.210 --> 25:37.710
I want to take this moment

25:37.710 --> 25:39.830
to register my objection
to this plan.

25:39.830 --> 25:42.540
Theft will not
reconcile these sisters.

25:42.540 --> 25:44.500
Well, what choice
do I have?

25:44.500 --> 25:47.120
I can't help anybody
from jail.

25:47.120 --> 25:48.540
Where do you get
your clothes?

25:48.540 --> 25:50.040
Do you shop?

25:50.040 --> 25:51.420
The mall.

25:51.420 --> 25:52.330
Really?

25:56.540 --> 25:58.170
Well, you always look nice.

25:58.170 --> 25:59.790
Very put together.

26:03.830 --> 26:07.580
♪♪

26:07.580 --> 26:11.330
♪♪

26:15.330 --> 26:16.830
Ohh!

26:16.830 --> 26:20.670
♪♪

26:20.670 --> 26:23.750
[ Glass breaks ]

26:23.750 --> 26:24.830
[ Body thuds ]

26:24.830 --> 26:29.620
♪♪

26:29.620 --> 26:34.670
♪♪

26:34.670 --> 26:39.420
♪♪

26:39.420 --> 26:44.170
♪♪

26:44.170 --> 26:49.880
♪♪

26:49.880 --> 26:51.620
[ Knock on window ]
Kevin!

26:51.620 --> 26:54.500
Uh! Ohh!

26:54.500 --> 26:55.420
Kevin!

26:55.420 --> 26:57.080
Ohh, no!

26:57.080 --> 27:00.330
Get out!
The cops are coming!

27:00.330 --> 27:01.620
Run!

27:01.620 --> 27:03.540
[ Siren wailing in distance ]
[ Gasps ]

27:03.540 --> 27:05.290
[ Panting ]

27:08.750 --> 27:10.040
[ Metal clanks ]

27:10.040 --> 27:11.830
[ Wailing continues ]

27:11.830 --> 27:13.420
What are you doing here?
-Run! Go!

27:13.420 --> 27:14.790
No, no, no.
Come on, come on, come on.

27:14.790 --> 27:16.080
Boost.

27:16.080 --> 27:21.210
♪♪

27:21.210 --> 27:22.670
Hurry. Come over.

27:22.670 --> 27:25.000
No, you know what, you go.
I'll get them to follow me.

27:25.000 --> 27:27.670
No! K-Kevin!

27:27.670 --> 27:29.460
[ High-pitched ]
He went that way!

27:31.790 --> 27:35.000
[ Tires screeching ]

27:35.000 --> 27:36.880
Officer: We've got eyes on.
Suspect on foot.

27:36.880 --> 27:38.750
All right,
I'll cut him off.

27:38.750 --> 27:43.420
♪♪

27:43.420 --> 27:45.500
No!
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

27:45.500 --> 27:47.000
Not now.

27:47.000 --> 27:50.960
Please, please, please,
don't, don't.

27:56.620 --> 27:58.000
No, no, no.

28:05.120 --> 28:07.710
[ Siren wailing ]

28:07.710 --> 28:10.620
[ Tires screech ]

28:10.620 --> 28:14.670
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:14.670 --> 28:17.380
[ Dulcimer music plays ]

28:17.380 --> 28:21.920
♪♪

28:21.920 --> 28:26.710
♪♪

28:26.710 --> 28:31.250
♪♪

28:31.250 --> 28:36.040
♪♪

28:36.040 --> 28:37.670
You!
Put your hands up!

28:37.670 --> 28:40.210
[ Baby crying ]

28:40.210 --> 28:41.880
I said put
your hands up now!

28:41.880 --> 28:43.920
Wait. Are you real?

28:43.920 --> 28:45.540
[ Electricity crackling ]

28:45.540 --> 28:47.080
[ Gurgles ]

28:49.710 --> 28:53.540
♪♪

28:53.540 --> 28:55.710
Ohh!

28:55.710 --> 28:58.080
Ow!

29:01.920 --> 29:04.540
Hey.
How's it going?

29:10.420 --> 29:13.040
This is Texas, right?

29:21.250 --> 29:22.670
[ Gasps ]

29:27.790 --> 29:29.540
Was I asleep?

29:29.540 --> 29:33.080
You, uh,
had your eyes closed.

29:33.080 --> 29:34.620
[ Sighs ]

29:34.620 --> 29:36.420
What?

29:36.420 --> 29:38.620
Oh, I'm sorry.
I wasn't talking to you.

29:38.620 --> 29:40.420
Uh...

29:40.420 --> 29:44.210
Oh, hey, so I got my vision
for some reason.

29:44.210 --> 29:47.250
Conveniently, while I was
getting chased by the cops.

29:47.250 --> 29:48.790
W-What did you see?

29:48.790 --> 29:51.380
Some kind of marketplace.

29:51.380 --> 29:55.290
Um, it might have been in Asia
or some-- something.

29:55.290 --> 29:56.880
That's --
That's all I remember.

29:56.880 --> 29:58.330
Did you see any writing,

29:58.330 --> 30:00.380
anything that would
tell you more?

30:00.380 --> 30:02.580
Nope.

30:02.580 --> 30:04.580
But I-I-I don't
understand.

30:04.580 --> 30:06.500
Why would I get
my vision now?

30:06.500 --> 30:08.620
All I did was
screw everything up.

30:08.620 --> 30:11.500
Yeah, you are good
at doing that.

30:11.500 --> 30:13.170
When you say things
like that,

30:13.170 --> 30:15.290
it makes me feel
like you're not paying attention

30:15.290 --> 30:16.330
to my feelings again.

30:16.330 --> 30:17.960
Maybe I'm just --

30:17.960 --> 30:22.120
Hey, I want a different cell.
This guy's crazy.

30:22.120 --> 30:24.960
Nate, I know
how this looks.

30:24.960 --> 30:27.960
I don't think you do, Kevin.
You are in very serious trouble.

30:27.960 --> 30:29.290
So is your partner.

30:29.290 --> 30:31.580
My partner?

30:31.580 --> 30:35.620
Amy doesn't deserve this
from either of you.

30:35.620 --> 30:38.210
Oh, no! Nate, Nate, no!
She didn't do anything wrong!

30:38.210 --> 30:39.830
Nate, come on! Nate!

30:39.830 --> 30:42.750
[ Sighs ]

30:42.750 --> 30:45.210
You can slip those off.

30:50.330 --> 30:52.620
Reese, what were you
doing out there?

30:52.620 --> 30:53.710
Nothing.

30:53.710 --> 30:55.620
Your uncle's
in a lot of trouble.

30:55.620 --> 30:57.540
But I don't believe
you were involved.

30:57.540 --> 30:59.500
He didn't do anything
wrong.

30:59.500 --> 31:01.750
He broke into a house
and destroyed property.

31:01.750 --> 31:04.580
I just think he probably
had a good reason for it.

31:04.580 --> 31:06.330
Why were you with him?

31:06.330 --> 31:09.330
I wanted to see
what he was up to.

31:09.330 --> 31:12.710
[ Sighs ]

31:12.710 --> 31:14.710
Some advice?

31:14.710 --> 31:17.330
Your mom has plenty on her plate
with Kevin.

31:17.330 --> 31:20.000
Please don't make her worry
about you, too.

31:22.290 --> 31:27.000
Let her know
where you are.

31:27.000 --> 31:29.790
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:29.790 --> 31:31.120
[ Dial tone ]

31:35.080 --> 31:38.000
[ Telephone ringing ]

31:38.000 --> 31:41.750
Hey, Mom, it's me -- Reese.

31:41.750 --> 31:43.830
I've got some bad news.

31:43.830 --> 31:45.250
Who is this?

31:45.250 --> 31:47.460
It's Reese, Mom.

31:47.460 --> 31:48.960
I'm with Kevin.

31:48.960 --> 31:50.290
We got arrested.

31:50.290 --> 31:52.040
Am I on the radio?

31:54.210 --> 31:55.540
Here you go.

31:55.540 --> 31:57.670
Tyler, listen to me.

31:57.670 --> 32:00.080
Kevin got arrested for breaking
into your boss' house.

32:00.080 --> 32:01.750
You have to do something.

32:01.750 --> 32:03.500
I'm on it.

32:06.170 --> 32:07.710
Okay, ma'am,
that's everything.

32:07.710 --> 32:10.250
We'll get out
of your hair.

32:10.250 --> 32:11.960
You want any help
cleaning up the mess?

32:13.380 --> 32:15.960
Clean my house?

32:15.960 --> 32:17.330
Sure.

32:17.330 --> 32:19.750
Let's just start
with the 5'6" turd

32:19.750 --> 32:21.790
standing in the middle
of the living room.

32:21.790 --> 32:24.380
[ Sighs ] I'm 5'11".

32:30.000 --> 32:31.580
[ Knock on door ]

32:33.580 --> 32:36.580
How many times do I have to tell
you that I don't wan--

32:38.540 --> 32:39.920
What the hell do you want?

32:39.920 --> 32:42.170
Lucille, we need to talk.

32:42.170 --> 32:46.960
You are the absolute last person
I want to listen to now or ever!

32:46.960 --> 32:47.830
[ Strong-arms door ]

32:49.710 --> 32:52.920
For once in your life, you're
gonna listen to me, Lucille.

32:52.920 --> 32:54.880
Am I making myself
perfectly clear?!

32:58.250 --> 32:59.670
Thanks!

33:03.580 --> 33:08.830
♪♪

33:08.830 --> 33:10.080
Nate, can we just talk?

33:10.080 --> 33:12.500
I will tell you everything
that I'm able to tell you.

33:12.500 --> 33:14.080
Come with me.

33:21.170 --> 33:22.500
Reese,
are you all right?

33:22.500 --> 33:24.710
Fine.

33:24.710 --> 33:26.960
What's going on?

33:26.960 --> 33:29.460
Ms. Russo is
dropping all charges.

33:29.460 --> 33:31.290
Claims you've been running
errands for her,

33:31.290 --> 33:33.000
and this is all a big, old
misunderstanding.

33:33.000 --> 33:35.620
That sound about right?

33:35.620 --> 33:38.790
Uh, yeah. Yep.

33:38.790 --> 33:42.170
Sure.
He's my little errand moron.

33:42.170 --> 33:44.210
Well, aren't we
a big, happy family?

33:44.210 --> 33:46.790
Right?!
Everything works out!

33:46.790 --> 33:49.080
Ms. Russo, if you could come
with me, sign some paperwork?

33:52.670 --> 33:53.790
All right.

33:53.790 --> 33:55.330
What just happened?

33:55.330 --> 33:58.540
Well, I was thinking about
how great you negotiated

33:58.540 --> 34:02.040
for my new car that got wrecked,
so I negotiated with Lucille.

34:02.040 --> 34:04.040
You did? How?

34:04.040 --> 34:06.420
I forced my way into her house,
locked the door,

34:06.420 --> 34:08.880
and told her I would quit
if she didn't fix this.

34:08.880 --> 34:10.380
And she agreed.

34:10.380 --> 34:11.830
Wow.

34:11.830 --> 34:15.540
Tyler, that's -- I mean,
it might be a little illegal,

34:15.540 --> 34:16.960
but it's amazing.

34:16.960 --> 34:20.580
Well, hey, hardball, Kev.
Just like you taught me.

34:20.580 --> 34:22.500
You're all free to go.

34:22.500 --> 34:26.080
Thank you, Nate.
Sorry.

34:27.250 --> 34:29.290
You called your mom, huh?

34:29.290 --> 34:34.040
♪♪

34:34.040 --> 34:38.790
♪♪

34:38.790 --> 34:43.540
♪♪

34:43.540 --> 34:48.540
♪♪

34:48.540 --> 34:50.000
Amy: Hey.

34:50.000 --> 34:53.790
Perfect timing.
How do you feel about painting?

34:53.790 --> 34:57.000
Uh, wish I could.
I'm...working.

34:57.000 --> 34:58.960
-Oh.
-Where's Reese?

34:58.960 --> 35:02.380
She was supposed to be helping,
but she has drama today.

35:02.380 --> 35:04.830
They're rehearsing.
I'm not complaining, though.

35:04.830 --> 35:06.790
I'm glad she's getting involved.

35:06.790 --> 35:08.000
Amy, about that,
I need --

35:08.000 --> 35:09.460
You know,
it's the funniest thing.

35:09.460 --> 35:12.290
All of that bad stuff
that happened --

35:12.290 --> 35:15.380
It's like I'm finally
coming out of it, you know?

35:15.380 --> 35:17.460
Reese is getting back
into her life,

35:17.460 --> 35:21.500
and Kevin is being less...
Kevin than usual.

35:21.500 --> 35:23.750
And you've been amazing.

35:23.750 --> 35:25.710
Things are good.

35:25.710 --> 35:28.380
♪♪

35:28.380 --> 35:29.960
[ Sighs ]

35:29.960 --> 35:31.710
Nate, are you okay?

35:33.670 --> 35:36.670
Uh, someone...found
Reese's cell.

35:36.670 --> 35:38.540
Uh, here.
-Oh.

35:38.540 --> 35:40.620
Here it is. They turned it in
to the station.

35:40.620 --> 35:42.460
Oh, my gosh. I cannot believe
that she lost this.

35:42.460 --> 35:43.920
I seriously thought
this thing

35:43.920 --> 35:45.460
was permanently attached
to her hand.

35:45.460 --> 35:46.880
[ Chuckles ]
Well, there it is.

35:46.880 --> 35:48.080
Thanks.

35:50.170 --> 35:52.620
Are you sure you're okay?

35:52.620 --> 35:55.080
Oh. Yeah.
Yeah, I'm good.

35:55.080 --> 35:57.290
You know what,
I'm gonna go on lunch.

35:57.290 --> 35:58.710
Paint in the garage?

35:58.710 --> 36:01.080
Uh, yes!
Thank you!

36:05.580 --> 36:07.210
Here you go.

36:07.210 --> 36:09.750
Thanks.

36:09.750 --> 36:11.670
What's eating you, Kev?

36:11.670 --> 36:14.210
[ Sighs ]

36:14.210 --> 36:19.120
I just...don't even know what
this was all about.

36:19.120 --> 36:20.880
Lucille's
never gonna change.

36:20.880 --> 36:22.000
I broke her clock.

36:22.000 --> 36:23.960
And I was kind of
a huge jerk to you.

36:23.960 --> 36:25.580
Oh, you? When?

36:25.580 --> 36:27.710
[ Chuckles ]

36:27.710 --> 36:30.620
You're a good person, Ty.
Don't ever change that.

36:30.620 --> 36:34.250
It's just...
It's a hard life for a nice guy.

36:34.250 --> 36:35.960
[ Chuckles ] Ain't it?

36:35.960 --> 36:38.460
You know, the only reason
Lucille dropped the charges

36:38.460 --> 36:40.540
against you is 'cause
she didn't want to lose me.

36:40.540 --> 36:42.540
I'm her best friend.

36:42.540 --> 36:44.540
I might be her only friend.

36:44.540 --> 36:46.000
It feels pretty great.

36:46.000 --> 36:47.830
You're garbage, Tyler.

36:47.830 --> 36:49.380
Love ya, Luce!

36:49.380 --> 36:52.420
You look at the worst
people have to offer

36:52.420 --> 36:54.170
and only see the good.

36:54.170 --> 36:56.120
I wish
I was more like you.

36:56.120 --> 36:58.920
Kevin, you're perfect.

36:58.920 --> 37:00.290
[ Scoffs ]

37:00.290 --> 37:03.330
There she is!
Where's my clock, you hag?!

37:03.330 --> 37:05.670
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
How about we just...?

37:05.670 --> 37:07.620
You want it?
Here it is!

37:07.620 --> 37:10.170
It's all yours!

37:10.170 --> 37:12.250
Look what you did!
Daddy promised that to me!

37:12.250 --> 37:14.290
That's a lie!
He said it was mine!

37:14.290 --> 37:16.170
The two of you
have so much in common.

37:16.170 --> 37:17.460
Both: Shut up!

37:17.460 --> 37:20.120
You -- You were always
Daddy's favorite,

37:20.120 --> 37:21.880
and the one thing
he left for me

37:21.880 --> 37:24.040
you stole before he was
even in the ground!

37:24.040 --> 37:27.920
Me?! He'd only talk about what
a perfect daughter you were!

37:27.920 --> 37:29.790
At night,
I'd close my eyes,

37:29.790 --> 37:32.620
and I'd imagine a different
animal tearing you to shreds!

37:32.620 --> 37:36.330
I look forward to your funeral
even more than my son's wedding!

37:36.330 --> 37:38.750
I worshiped you.
I just wanted to be around you.

37:38.750 --> 37:40.960
You are delusional.
You -- You never liked me!

37:40.960 --> 37:42.790
Guys, guys, shut up,
shut up, shut up.

37:42.790 --> 37:45.420
I thought you said this was
a priceless German antique?

37:45.420 --> 37:47.460
Well, it was before you
destroyed it!

37:47.460 --> 37:50.290
Well, then why is it stamped
"Made in Michigan"

37:50.290 --> 37:52.790
on the inside?
-That's impossible.

37:54.500 --> 37:56.500
Why would he lie
about something so stupid?

37:59.830 --> 38:01.500
Why would he lie
about anything?

38:01.500 --> 38:03.290
I mean, "Best Bowler
in the League"?

38:03.290 --> 38:05.170
He got that trophy
at a pawnshop.

38:05.170 --> 38:06.380
Maybe he was lying
when he said

38:06.380 --> 38:07.880
he always wished
I'd been a boy.

38:07.880 --> 38:10.380
He told me that if he and mama
ever got divorced,

38:10.380 --> 38:12.620
he'd take you.

38:12.620 --> 38:15.500
I haven't forgotten about that
my whole life.

38:15.500 --> 38:19.170
I-I never heard that.
I'm sorry.

38:19.170 --> 38:21.420
Guys.

38:21.420 --> 38:22.710
This is so great.

38:22.710 --> 38:23.960
What a breakthrough.

38:23.960 --> 38:26.120
[ Sighs ]

38:26.120 --> 38:28.420
You know,
as bad as Daddy was,

38:28.420 --> 38:30.710
he wasn't as stupid
as this guy.

38:30.710 --> 38:33.170
Look at that face.
It's perfectly blank.

38:33.170 --> 38:35.830
Like he's constantly going into
or coming out of a coma.

38:35.830 --> 38:37.790
Hi, dum-dum!

38:37.790 --> 38:39.750
Both: Anyone home?

38:39.750 --> 38:41.670
[ Laughs ]

38:41.670 --> 38:43.750
Come on. Let me show you
around this place.

38:43.750 --> 38:44.710
[ Laughs ]

38:44.710 --> 38:46.080
Ahh.

38:46.080 --> 38:48.290
Aren't they great?

38:48.290 --> 38:50.080
Ty, they are
the spawn of Satan.

38:52.920 --> 38:55.420
[ Children playing ]

38:55.420 --> 38:59.830
♪♪

38:59.830 --> 39:02.420
We used to come here
when we were kids.

39:02.420 --> 39:06.500
I sailed little boats
in the water over there.

39:06.500 --> 39:10.040
Got to second base
with Laura French right there.

39:10.040 --> 39:13.000
Are we gonna walk through your
adolescent sexual experiences?

39:13.000 --> 39:15.790
Because, no, thank you.

39:15.790 --> 39:19.960
This is the place that I missed
when I was in New York.

39:19.960 --> 39:21.750
This was home.

39:21.750 --> 39:23.920
Oh.

39:23.920 --> 39:29.000
The thing I learned about home
is that it's not really a place.

39:29.000 --> 39:30.620
It's a feeling.

39:30.620 --> 39:33.580
And it doesn't really matter
where you are.

39:33.580 --> 39:36.830
It's about who you are
and who your friends are

39:36.830 --> 39:40.460
and --
and it's about food.

39:44.500 --> 39:47.170
Billy Roy's Texas Brisket.

39:48.750 --> 39:51.880
Dry-rubbed with 24 spices.

39:51.880 --> 39:54.250
Smoked over apple and hickory
for 10 hours.

39:54.250 --> 39:55.830
So tender it melts
in your mouth.

39:55.830 --> 39:57.250
I assume you can eat.

39:57.250 --> 39:59.170
Or I assume you can
figure it out.

40:02.040 --> 40:03.500
Mmm!

40:05.120 --> 40:08.000
[ Chuckles ]

40:08.000 --> 40:12.250
I-I know I can't understand
what you gave up to come here,

40:12.250 --> 40:15.960
but...maybe you can
find things

40:15.960 --> 40:19.210
that make you miss it
a little less.

40:19.210 --> 40:23.710
♪♪

40:23.710 --> 40:25.580
[ Sighs ]

40:25.580 --> 40:28.960
You ever see the sky
first thing in the morning

40:28.960 --> 40:32.710
after a big thunderstorm?

40:32.710 --> 40:34.330
That color?

40:34.330 --> 40:36.330
Yeah.

40:36.330 --> 40:38.250
[ Sighs ]

40:38.250 --> 40:40.620
That's what home is like.

40:40.620 --> 40:42.670
♪♪

40:42.670 --> 40:44.670
Wow.

40:44.670 --> 40:47.290
And -- And you're right.
It's not the place.

40:47.290 --> 40:49.330
It's the feeling.
Peace.

40:49.330 --> 40:52.540
[ Sighs ]

40:52.540 --> 40:54.920
Boundless, enduring peace.

40:54.920 --> 40:56.750
♪♪

40:56.750 --> 40:58.580
And that's what I miss.

40:58.580 --> 41:00.710
♪♪

41:00.710 --> 41:02.120
But this is nice, too.

41:02.120 --> 41:04.670
[ Chuckles ]
Well, go on. Try it.

41:04.670 --> 41:06.620
Do you eat things?

41:06.620 --> 41:08.420
-I eat things!
-Okay. Okay.

41:08.420 --> 41:09.880
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

41:09.880 --> 41:11.290
[ Clears throat ]

41:11.290 --> 41:15.830
♪♪

41:15.830 --> 41:16.830
I mean...

41:16.830 --> 41:18.080
Mmm!

41:18.080 --> 41:19.830
[ Both laugh ]

41:19.830 --> 41:21.290
You're right!

41:21.290 --> 41:22.830
-I knew it.
-Mm-hmm!

41:22.830 --> 41:25.040
[ Laughs ]
A little piece of heaven!

41:25.040 --> 41:26.790
That --
That is what I'm saying!

41:26.790 --> 41:29.000
[ Laughs ]

41:29.000 --> 41:30.380
Mm.

41:30.380 --> 41:33.120
Oh.
-I don't even know what it is.

41:33.120 --> 41:34.670
It's got to be
some kind of magic.

41:34.670 --> 41:36.500
One of the 24 spices is --

41:36.500 --> 41:38.920
-Oh, didn't go 25.
-Probably tried 25.

41:38.920 --> 41:40.120
Yeah, didn't work.

41:43.790 --> 41:45.580
[ Clears throat ]
How was rehearsal?

41:45.580 --> 41:46.670
Good.

41:46.670 --> 41:47.880
What part are you?

41:47.880 --> 41:50.120
Stagehand.
I didn't try out.

41:50.120 --> 41:51.500
Next time, maybe.

41:51.500 --> 41:52.960
[ Chuckles ] Cool.

41:52.960 --> 41:57.420
So, um, I was wondering if you
could stop following me around.

41:57.420 --> 41:59.420
I appreciate
the interest,

41:59.420 --> 42:02.330
but, uh, it's -- it's
weird...and creepy.

42:02.330 --> 42:03.670
Okay.

42:03.670 --> 42:04.920
Thank you.

42:04.920 --> 42:07.380
Can I ask you a question?

42:07.380 --> 42:09.080
Shoot.

42:11.420 --> 42:13.710
Did that meteor
give you superpowers?

42:13.710 --> 42:16.500
[ Inhales ]

42:16.500 --> 42:18.500
Hmm...

42:26.710 --> 42:31.460
♪♪

42:31.460 --> 42:35.960
♪♪

42:35.960 --> 42:40.460
♪♪

42:40.460 --> 42:45.290
♪♪

42:45.290 --> 42:49.790
♪♪

42:49.790 --> 42:55.120
♪♪
